elements.text:
[*] Encapsulation is the technique of protecting data by keeping fields private 
and exposing only necessary methods to interact with them

elements.text:
[*] It’s like wrapping data (variables) and code (methods) together into a single unit — the class
 — and controlling access using access modifiers.
